snippet.title: RUHE IN FRIEDEN MAYTRIXX😭💔
snippet.description:
RUHE IN FRIEDEN MAYTRIXXX 😭💔


Hey Maytrixx, mein Freund. Meine Gedanken kreisen jeden Tag um dich. Ich habe das Verlangen, dir zu schreiben und dich zu fragen, wie es dir geht. 😭 Leider ist das nicht mehr möglich und das bricht mir das Herz. 💔😢
Ich wollte dir die letzte Ehre erweisen und ein Lied in der Location spielen, wo du auch viele Male gespielt hast und wir uns oft gesehen haben. 😢😢😢
Bruder, mach den Himmel zu deiner Stage. Wir sehen uns bald wieder. ❤️❤️❤️ Niemand wird dich hier vergessen!!! RUHE IN FRIEDEN!
Ich hab dich lieb. 🫶🥹😭

snippet.title: The Devil Wears Prada 2 | Official Trailer
snippet.description:
Everybody wants this. 

Meryl Streep, Anne Hathaway, Emily Blunt, and Stanley Tucci return in The Devil Wears Prada 2, in theaters May 1. Watch the full trailer now. 

Almost 20 years after making their iconic turn as Miranda, Andy, Emily and Nigel—Meryl Streep, Anne Hathaway, Emily Blunt and Stanley Tucci return to the fashionable streets of New York City and the sleek offices of Runway Magazine in the eagerly awaited sequel to the 2006 phenomenon that defined a generation. 
 
The film reunites the original main cast with director David Frankel and writer Aline Brosh McKenna, and introduces an all-new runway of characters including Kenneth Branagh, Simone Ashley, Justin Theroux, Lucy Liu, Patrick Brammall, Caleb Hearon, Helen J. Shen, Pauline Chalamet, B.J. Novak and Conrad Ricamora. Tracie Thoms and Tibor Feldman also reprise their roles as “Lily” and “Irv” from the first film. 
 
“The Devil Wears Prada 2” is produced by Wendy Finerman, and executive produced by Michael Bederman, Karen Rosenfelt and Aline Brosh McKenna. The film debuts exclusively in theaters May 1.

snippet.title: THE DEVIL WEARS PRADA 2 | Official Trailer (2026) 4K
snippet.description:
A sequel? For spring? Groundbreaking. Meryl Streep, Anne Hathaway, Emily Blunt, and Stanley Tucci return in The Devil Wears Prada 2, in theaters May 1, 2026. Watch the teaser trailer now. 

Almost twenty years after making their iconic turns as Miranda, Andy, Emily and Nigel—Meryl Streep, Anne Hathaway, Emily Blunt and Stanley Tucci return to the fashionable streets of New York City and the sleek offices of Runway Magazine in the eagerly awaited sequel to the 2006 phenomenon that defined a generation. 
 
The film reunites the original main cast with director David Frankel and writer Aline Brosh McKenna, and introduces an all-new runway of characters including Kenneth Branagh, Simone Ashley, Justin Theroux, Lucy Liu, Patrick Brammall, Caleb Hearon, Helen J. Shen, Pauline Chalamet, B.J. Novak and Conrad Ricamora. Tracie Thoms and Tibor Feldman also reprise their roles as “Lily” and “Irv” from the first film. 
 
“The Devil Wears Prada 2” is produced by Wendy Finerman, and executive produced by Michael Bederman, Karen Rosenfelt and McKenna. The film debuts exclusively in theaters May 1, 2026.

Wanna support us? Get your JoBlo Merch right here!
https://joblo-merch.creator-spring.com/

snippet.title: Noah Kahan - The Great Divide (Official Music Video)
snippet.description:
Watch the official music video for "The Great Divide" by Noah Kahan.

Stream/download "The Great Divide": https://noahkahan.lnk.to/thegreatdivide-single
Pre-order Noah's album, The Great Divide, out April 24: https://noahkahan.lnk.to/thegreatdivide

Created in partnership with Mastercard. Learn more: https://priceless.com/NoahKahan

Get notified about Noah Kahan's "The Great Divide Tour" here: https://noahkahan.com/pages/tour

Director: Parker Schmidt 
Creative Direction: Bridget Jewell, Dan Grech 
Creatives: Mihai Vasile, Tyler Bartley 
Producer: Judi Nierman

Follow Noah Kahan:
Linktree: https://linktr.ee/noahkahanmusic
Instagram: http://instagram.com/noahkahanmusic
Facebook: http://facebook.com/noahkahanmusic
TikTok: https://www.tiktok.com/@noahkahanmusic
Twitter: https://x.com/noahkahan

Lyrics: 
I can’t recall the last time that we talked
About anything but lookin’ out for cops
We got cigarette burns on the same side of our hands
But we ain't friends, we’re just morons
Who broke skin in the same spot

But I’ve never seen you take a turn that wide
And I’m high enough to still care if I die
So I tried to read the thoughts that you worked overtime to stop
You said fuck off, and I said nothing for a while

You know I think about you all the time
And my deep misunderstanding of your life
And how bad it must have been for you back then
And how hard it was to keep it all inside

I hope you settle down, I hope you marry rich
I hope you’re scared of only ordinary shit
Like murderers and ghosts and cancer on your skin
And not your soul, and what he might do with it

You inched yourself across the great divide
While we drove aimlessly along the Twin State line
I heard nothin' but the bass in every ballad that you'd play
While you swore to God the singer read your mind
But the world is scared of hesitatin' things
Yeah, they only shoot the birds who cannot sing
And I'm finally aware of how shitty and unfair
It was to stare ahead like everything was fine

You know I think about you all the time
And my deep misunderstanding of your life
And how bad it must have been for you back then
And how hard it was to keep it all inside

I hope you settle down, I hope you marry rich
I hope you’re scared of only ordinary shit
Like murderers and ghosts and cancer on your skin
And not your soul, and what he might do with it

Rage, in small ways
Did you wish that I could know?
You'd fade, to some place
I wasn't brave enough to go

I hope you settle down, I hope you marry rich
I hope you’re scared of only ordinary shit
Like murderers and ghosts and cancer on your skin
And not your soul, and what he might do with it
Aaah, ooh

I hope you threw a brick right into that stained glass
I hope you’re with someone who isn’t scared to ask
I hope that you’re not losing sleep about what’s next
Or about your soul, and what he might do with it

#noahkahan #thegreatdivide

snippet.title: Character Trailer - "Zibai: Mortal Flesh to Kindred Earth" | Genshin Impact #GenshinImpact #Zibai
snippet.description:
The Three Deadly Selves as specters come. In union born, in union quelled.
To hold a day as a passing year, illuminate the heart that was.
Singer: Alan

English Translation:
The moon, a jade plate, climbs the misty skies
Thin dewdrops gleam as they fall like sighs
Which grass shall never yellow in the fleeting day?
Which virtue lasts while seasons slip away?
Like drifting dust along the country way
The grass lies pale, the poplars sere, yet the end delays
By the roadside, the remnants keep their rites
As bronze statues of old lie lost in thorn and briar
All things keep their seasons, past all mortal measure
Passing through this mortal world like a waking dream
Like drifting shadows, fleeting, swift, and bright
Time races on, a white steed through the desolate plain
Its path unknown, its destination unseen
Which grass shall never yellow in the fleeting day?
Which virtue lasts while seasons slip away?
Like drifting dust along the country way
Alone with my staff, I cross the river on a single reed, like a lone wild goose in flight
Who says the river is too wide to cross?
Through shadowed reeds I seek the broken jade
The past cannot be undone, the road ahead stretches long
Friends spread the mat and share their wine, while distant fields of millet sway and shine
Some till the soil, some sow the seed — this is the life the people long to lead
In desolate courts, the withered grass sways in the moon's pale beam, and waning decay glimmers as fireflies' dream

snippet.title: Ruwa Jin - Jin Jin
snippet.description:
Ruwa Jin - “Jin Jin”

✦ Available on all streaming platforms:
🟢 Spotify:
⚪️ Apple Music:

Follow Ruwa Jin:
Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/ruwajin

“Jin Jin” speaks of a quiet, spiritual kind of love.
A presence that protects without control,
a soul that stays close when words fall silent.

The song reflects on being someone’s inner shelter -
not loud, not forceful, but constant.
Gentle Afrobeat rhythms meet soulful emotion,
creating a warm, spiritual calm between love and faith.

✦ Genre: afro-soul · spiritual afrobeat · emotional pop · ambient soul
✦ Mood: protective · warm · melancholic · spiritual · love
✦ Sound: soft percussion · gentle pads · emotional vocals · airy mix


📝 LYRICS:

[Intro]
Mm…
Yeah

[Verse 1]
You said love is like a flame
But we burn slow, never the same
You been searchin’ for a sign
But I’ve been right here, all the time

When you cry, I feel it too
Every breath, I walk with you
You don’t see, but deep inside
I’m the light you try to hide

[Chorus]
I’m your Jin Jin
Your peace when the rain falls in
I’m your Jin Jin
Your calm when the storm begins
I’m your Jin Jin
Your truth when your faith feels thin
I’m your Jin Jin
Forever within

[Verse 2]
I know your heart been bruised before
You closed the lock, then lost the door
But love don’t fade, it just transforms
From pain to light, from loss to warmth

I see the prayers you never said
The dreams still lying in your bed
You don’t need to face it all alone
You can rest, I’ll guide you home

[Chorus]
I’m your Jin Jin
Your peace when the rain falls in
I’m your Jin Jin
Your calm when the storm begins
I’m your Jin Jin
Your truth when your faith feels thin
I’m your Jin Jin
Forever within

[Bridge]
Even when the silence breaks
Even when the soul still aches
I’ll be there through every phase
Your light inside my waves

[Outro]
Mmm…
You don’t have to fight again
I’m your Jin Jin
Till the end

#ruwajin #jinjin #afrosoul #afrobeat #emotionalmusic #soulfulmusic #spiritualmusic #healing #newmusic2026 #melancholic #emotionalafrobeat #lovemusic
